snippet.textDisplay:
Man tinder really makes me uncomfortable. Just gets me so self-critical on what pictures I should use and having the perfect description because who’s gonna swipe on some goofy lookin’ guy who doesn’t like adventures or the office? I honestly think that distilling you’re whole individual personality and being down into 5 pictures and 280 characters is impossible.
And then when I actually get a match it’s like “RED ALERT RAISE SHEILDS FIRE PHOTON ONE LINERS” and it just doesn’t feel natural.
But at the same time meeting someone in person can seem so much harder because most people are out in public on their phones swiping away on tinder. And then if ya do meet someone you dig gotta spend months building a friendship. Or sometimes it takes you years of being friends before you both go “oh hey do we like each other more than just as friends?”
Dating is just confusing as fuck overall.
